quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  8,46,"And obey God and his Apostle; and dispute not, lest ye become fainthearted and your success go from you; but endure with steadfastness, for God is with the steadfastly enduring"
  8,47,"And be not like those Meccans who came out of their houses insolently and to be seen of men, and who turn others from the way of God: God is round about their actions"
  8,48,"When Satan prepared their works for them, and said, \"No man shall conquer you this day; and verily I will be near to help you:\" But when the two armies came in sight, he turned on his heel and said, \"Ay, I am clear of you: ay, I see what ye see not: ay, I fear God; for God is severe in punishing"
  8,49,"When the hypocrites and the diseased of heart said, \"Their Religion hath misled the Muslims: But whoso putteth his trust in God. , , , Yes, verily God is Mighty, Wise"
  8,50,"If thou didst see, when the angels cause the infidels to die! They smite their faces and their backs, and - \"Taste ye the torture of the burning"
  8,51,"This, for what your hands have sent on before you:\" - and God is not unjust to his servants"
  8,52,"Their state is like that of the people of Pharaoh and of those before them who believed not in the signs of God: therefore God seized upon them in their sin! God is Mighty, severe in punishing"